article.headline: N. Carolina A&T 80, SMU 76
article.story: DALLAS (AP) -- Steven Rush came off the bench to score 22 points, including six 3-pointers, in North Carolina A&T's 80-76 win over SMU on Saturday night. Rush led the Aggies (4-9) with seven rebounds. Nicholas Wilson had 16 points off the bench and Jason Wills added 11 -- nine on free throws. Austin Ewing, the only Aggies starter to score in the double digits, had 10 points, including three 3-pointers. The Aggies, who converted 14 Mustangs turnovers into 20 points, led 36-28 at halftime. Brian Epps scored a career-high 19 points for the Mustangs (9-3), while Cameron Spencer set his own record of 10 rebounds. Ike Ofoegbu came off the bench to score 15 points. He was 10-of-12 from the free-throw line. Jon Killen had 14 points, including three 3-pointers.
